name: CustomXmlPart
description: Represents a custom XML part object in a workbook.

properties.name: namespaceUri
properties.description: The custom XML part's namespace URI.

methods.name: getXml
methods.description: Gets the custom XML part's full XML content.

methods.name: setXml
methods.description: Sets the custom XML part's full XML content.

parameters.name: xml
parameters.description: XML content to set.

methods.name: insertElement
methods.description: Inserts the given XML under the parent element identified by xpath at child position index.
methods.signature: insertElement(xpath: string, xml: string, namespaceMappings: object, index: number)

parameters.name: xpath
parameters.description: Absolute path to the parent element in XPath notation.

parameters.name: xml
parameters.description: XML content to be inserted.

parameters.name: namespaceMappings
parameters.description: An object whose properties represent namespace aliases and the values are the actual namespace URIs.

parameters.name: index
parameters.description: Zero-based position at which the new XML to be inserted. If omitted, the XML will be appended as the last child of this parent.

methods.name: updateElement
methods.description: Updates the XML of the element identified by xpath.
methods.signature: updateElement(xpath: string, xml: string, namespaceMappings: object)

parameters.name: xpath
parameters.description: Absolute path to the element in XPath notation.

parameters.name: xml
parameters.description: New XML content to be stored.

parameters.name: namespaceMappings
parameters.description: An object whose properties represent namespace aliases and the values are the actual namespace URIs.

methods.name: deleteElement
methods.description: Deletes the element identified by xpath.

parameters.name: xpath
parameters.description: Absolute path to the element in XPath notation.

parameters.name: namespaceMappings
parameters.description: An object whose properties represent namespace aliases and the values are the actual namespace URIs.

parameters.name: xpath
parameters.description: An XPath query.

parameters.name: namespaceMappings
parameters.description: An object whose properties represent namespace aliases and the values are the actual namespace URIs.

methods.name: insertAttribute
methods.description: Inserts an attribute with the given name and value to the element identified by xpath.
methods.signature: insertAttribute(xpath: string, namespaceMappings: object, name: string, value: string)

parameters.name: xpath
parameters.description: Absolute path to the element in XPath notation.

parameters.name: namespaceMappings
parameters.description: An object whose properties represent namespace aliases and the values are the actual namespace URIs.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: Name of the attribute.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: Value of the attribute.

methods.name: updateAttribute
methods.description: Updates the value of an attribute with the given name of the element identified by xpath.
methods.signature: updateAttribute(xpath: string, namespaceMappings: object, name: string, value: string)

parameters.name: xpath
parameters.description: Absolute path to the element in XPath notation.

parameters.name: namespaceMappings
parameters.description: An object whose properties represent namespace aliases and the values are the actual namespace URIs.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: Name of the attribute.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: New value of the attribute.

methods.name: deleteAttribute
methods.description: Deletes an attribute with the given name from the element identified by xpath.
methods.signature: deleteAttribute(xpath: string, namespaceMappings: object, name: string)

parameters.name: xpath
parameters.description: Absolute path to the element in XPath notation.

parameters.name: namespaceMappings
parameters.description: An object whose properties represent namespace aliases and the values are the actual namespace URIs.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: Name of the attribute.

methods.name: load
methods.description: Fills the proxy object created in JavaScript layer with property and object values specified in the parameter.

parameters.name: param
parameters.description: Accepts parameter and relationship names as delimited string or an array. Or, provide [loadOption](loadoption.md) object.
